1
00:01:00,583 --> 00:01:01,625
[MOSUKE]
Tell us, Elder...

2
00:01:01,708 --> 00:01:03,375
What's the news from
the Priestess?

3
00:01:03,458 --> 00:01:04,958
Is she bringing us Samurai?

4
00:01:05,041 --> 00:01:06,958
She promises
she will not fail us.

5
00:01:07,041 --> 00:01:09,416
She's going to find
seven, and then return.

6
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:11,500
Great Samurai,
you're beautiful... 

7
00:01:11,583 --> 00:01:13,916
So beautiful...
that I'm in love.

8
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:16,541
Heh, heh... Your diction's
perfect--like a pro...

9
00:01:16,625 --> 00:01:19,083
But your delivery needs
some work. Ha, ha, ha...

10
00:01:19,166 --> 00:01:23,166
Great Samurai, you're beautiful!
So beautiful I'm in love!

11
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:26,333
That's the spirit!
You're alright man! Ha, ha, ha!

12
00:01:28,125 --> 00:01:30,000
I know--chopping 
wood with my sword...

13
00:01:30,083 --> 00:01:32,708
...hardly lives up to
the whole samurai tradition.

14
00:01:32,791 --> 00:01:34,041
Nonsense...

15
00:01:34,125 --> 00:01:36,416
Looks like a lot more fun
than chopping up people.

16
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:38,333
So what does that make you...?

17
00:01:38,416 --> 00:01:40,375
The King of Monkey Mountain?

18
00:01:40,458 --> 00:01:42,333
[HYOGO YELLS]

19
00:01:43,083 --> 00:01:44,458
[KIRARA SCREAMS]

20
00:01:45,291 --> 00:01:46,416
No!

21
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,083
[KIRARA SCREAMS]

22
00:01:52,166 --> 00:01:52,833
[KATSUSHIRO GRUNTS]

23
00:01:52,916 --> 00:01:54,875
[MARO]
What?! Envoy!

24
00:01:56,416 --> 00:01:58,500
[MARO YELLS]

25
00:02:06,416 --> 00:02:11,375
♪ opening song ♪

26
00:03:41,541 --> 00:03:43,166
[PATROLMAN A] The wound
spans from the right shoulder

27
00:03:43,250 --> 00:03:44,291
to the left hip.

28
00:03:44,375 --> 00:03:46,666
Classic cut, with
a very sharp blade.

29
00:03:46,750 --> 00:03:48,666
Chances are he lay
suffering for some time

30
00:03:48,750 --> 00:03:50,041
while he bled to death.

31
00:03:50,125 --> 00:03:52,000
[TESSAI] Hmm...

32
00:03:53,416 --> 00:03:56,250
[UKYO GRUNTS]

33
00:03:58,333 --> 00:04:00,000
Young master
you mustn't.

34
00:04:00,083 --> 00:04:01,625
It's dangerous.

35
00:04:01,708 --> 00:04:02,875
[UKYO]
You're no fun.

36
00:04:02,958 --> 00:04:04,000
This is no toy,

37
00:04:04,083 --> 00:04:06,333
it's an important
piece of evidence.

38
00:04:07,083 --> 00:04:09,625
Ukyo, perhaps you
should wait outside...

39
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:12,333
I wouldn't want your delicate
sensibilities to be offended

40
00:04:12,416 --> 00:04:14,458
by such a scene.

41
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,375
[TESSAI] My Lord.

42
00:04:21,458 --> 00:04:22,875
It doesn't make sense.

43
00:04:22,958 --> 00:04:24,625
How could such a highly
skilled swordsman

44
00:04:24,708 --> 00:04:26,666
be imprudent enough to
leave the murder weapon

45
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:28,416
at the scene of the crime?

46
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:30,416
Did this sword commit murder?

47
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:31,666
What?

48
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:34,166
I'm asking if this sword
magically walked in here

49
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:38,458
of its own volition and
killed the Imperial Envoy.

50
00:04:38,541 --> 00:04:41,916
The question is... what type
of person carries a sword?

51
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,708
A samurai
does, My Lord.

52
00:04:43,791 --> 00:04:45,625
Then I want you
to arrest all samurai.

53
00:04:45,708 --> 00:04:46,833
Begging your
pardon Lord,

54
00:04:46,916 --> 00:04:48,041
but shouldn't we
narrow it down

55
00:04:48,125 --> 00:04:50,333
to a handful of
possible suspects?

56
00:04:50,416 --> 00:04:52,750
When searching for
one single grain of sand,

57
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:55,000
a wise man will choose
to run the entire beach

58
00:04:55,083 --> 00:04:56,208
through a sieve.

59
00:04:56,291 --> 00:04:57,375
Understand?

60
00:04:57,458 --> 00:04:59,250
[TESSAI]
Yes my lord.

61
00:05:01,791 --> 00:05:05,583
I suppose those two are no
longer considered samurai then?

62
00:05:14,916 --> 00:05:18,000
On your feet, you are
all under arrest for murder!

63
00:05:18,083 --> 00:05:19,000
Just try...!

64
00:05:19,083 --> 00:05:20,541
Merchant patrolmen
and their sticks

65
00:05:20,625 --> 00:05:23,000
are no match for the
samurai warrior's blade.

66
00:05:23,083 --> 00:05:24,666
Your compliance or your life.

67
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:26,000
What?!

68
00:05:26,083 --> 00:05:28,208
[SAMURAI B YELLS]

69
00:05:28,291 --> 00:05:29,916
Consider this your warning!

70
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,625
All samurai will be
taken, dead or alive!

71
00:05:32,708 --> 00:05:35,000
[FIGHTING SOUNDS]

72
00:05:35,083 --> 00:05:36,916
[SAMURAI C SCREAMS]

73
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,041
[SAMURAI D] Move!

74
00:05:45,291 --> 00:05:46,500
[SAMURAI D YELLS]

75
00:05:51,041 --> 00:05:52,208
[ANNOUNCER]
Attention.

76
00:05:52,291 --> 00:05:54,208
An Imperial Envoy has
been brutally murdered

77
00:05:54,291 --> 00:05:55,708
in the Magistrate's house,

78
00:05:55,791 --> 00:05:59,708
and evidence shows the
assassin was, in fact, samurai.

79
00:05:59,791 --> 00:06:01,541
In response to
this heinous act,

80
00:06:01,625 --> 00:06:03,541
the Magistrate has
launched a citywide hunt

81
00:06:03,625 --> 00:06:05,958
for all remnants of
the warrior class.

82
00:06:06,041 --> 00:06:08,375
For those who provide valid
information concerning

83
00:06:08,458 --> 00:06:09,916
the whereabouts of samurai,

84
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,833
there will be a reward
of ten bundles of rice.

85
00:06:12,916 --> 00:06:15,333
For an actual capture,
one hundred bundles.

86
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:18,041
Regardless of whether
they are dead or alive.

87
00:06:18,125 --> 00:06:19,958
You're kidding me.

88
00:06:22,541 --> 00:06:25,000
I see...that explains things.

89
00:06:25,083 --> 00:06:26,416
A hundred
bundles of rice--

90
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:28,125
that's a much better
deal than we're getting.

91
00:06:28,208 --> 00:06:30,291
Wonder if I can
turn myself in.

92
00:06:30,375 --> 00:06:32,291
I'm sorry
you're in trouble.

93
00:06:32,375 --> 00:06:33,916
Don't be so negative, man!

94
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:36,083
At times like these
one should just laugh!

95
00:06:36,166 --> 00:06:38,041
Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha!

96
00:06:38,125 --> 00:06:40,333
[RIKICHI LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

97
00:06:41,666 --> 00:06:48,125
[ONLOOKERS WHISPER]

98
00:06:48,208 --> 00:06:51,083
It appears the road ahead of
us will lead to more trouble.

99
00:06:51,166 --> 00:06:53,000
Trouble often
begets good fortune

100
00:06:53,083 --> 00:06:55,083
when you least expect
it, my friend.

101
00:06:55,166 --> 00:06:57,125
Do you know
something I don't?

102
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:59,625
Any samurai foolish
enough to be caught

103
00:06:59,708 --> 00:07:02,125
isn't worth our time
to begin with.

104
00:07:02,208 --> 00:07:04,541
[GOROBEI]
I see... Excellent point.

105
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,833
[KIKUCHIYO]
Let go of me, you jackasses!

106
00:07:09,916 --> 00:07:11,833
Didn't your mothers ever
teach you any manners?!

107
00:07:11,916 --> 00:07:14,958
This isn't how you treat
a guest you know!

108
00:07:15,041 --> 00:07:16,541
[PATROLMAN B]
Keep it down!

109
00:07:16,625 --> 00:07:20,291
[KIKUCHIYO] Hey! You scratched
my metal, you pea-brained goats!

110
00:07:20,375 --> 00:07:23,250
You're gonna' pay
my repair bill! Hey!

111
00:07:23,333 --> 00:07:24,583
Where are you going...?!

112
00:07:24,666 --> 00:07:27,916
Can you at least
bring me my sword?

113
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:30,916
Ah... Bastards.

114
00:07:34,083 --> 00:07:36,333
I got captured on purpose.

115
00:07:36,416 --> 00:07:39,041
What...? Why would
you do such a thing?

116
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:41,250
[KIKUCHIYO]
Isn't it obvious, old man?

117
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:44,333
I'm here to help you poor
fools make a prison break.

118
00:07:44,416 --> 00:07:45,458
Prison break?

119
00:07:45,541 --> 00:07:46,833
[KIKUCHIYO]
Sure...!

120
00:07:46,916 --> 00:07:48,833
But I need you to do
something for me in return...

121
00:07:48,916 --> 00:07:51,541
I'll explain once
we're out of here... Deal?

122
00:07:51,625 --> 00:07:54,291
I would like nothing more,
if it were possible.

123
00:07:54,375 --> 00:07:56,500
[KIKUCHIYO]
Possible?! Heh...

124
00:07:58,958 --> 00:08:01,458
Heh... What do you call that?

125
00:08:01,541 --> 00:08:02,625
[SAMURAI GROUP LAUGHS]

126
00:08:02,708 --> 00:08:03,666
[PATROLMAN B] Huh...?

127
00:08:03,750 --> 00:08:05,041
[SAMURAI GROUP] Get 'em!

128
00:08:07,875 --> 00:08:09,333
[KIKUCHIYO]
Let's do this!

129
00:08:09,416 --> 00:08:10,916
[SAMURAI GROUP] Yeah!

130
00:08:13,041 --> 00:08:15,916
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

131
00:08:17,291 --> 00:08:19,500
[KIKUCHIYO] Come on!

132
00:08:28,958 --> 00:08:31,041
[KIRARA]
Welcome back.

133
00:08:31,125 --> 00:08:33,041
[KOMACHI]
Bring us any samurai?

134
00:08:33,125 --> 00:08:35,416
[HEIHACHI] The samurai
store was fresh out...

135
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:36,958
...but the candy shop wasn't.

136
00:08:37,041 --> 00:08:39,875
Thank you, red's my favorite!

137
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:43,750
Heihachi... that was
so generous of you.

138
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:47,208
[HEIHACHI] Aw, it's my
pleasure. Don't mention it.

139
00:08:47,291 --> 00:08:49,208
So... no luck?

140
00:08:49,291 --> 00:08:51,791
I'd call that
an understatement.

141
00:08:51,875 --> 00:08:53,708
It's because of
the samurai hunt.

142
00:08:53,791 --> 00:08:55,208
The samurai hunt?

143
00:08:55,291 --> 00:08:58,208
Mm-Hmm... Apparently we all
teamed up to kill an envoy--

144
00:08:58,291 --> 00:09:01,000
any samurai who aren't
in jail are in hiding now.

145
00:09:01,083 --> 00:09:03,208
Don't worry, we'll
think of something.

146
00:09:03,291 --> 00:09:07,208
[KIKUCHIYO] Hey guys!
Check out what I found!

147
00:09:12,458 --> 00:09:13,666
[HEIHACHI]
Kikuchiyo-dono!

148
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:15,333
[GOROBEI]
You're kidding me.

149
00:09:15,416 --> 00:09:18,000
[KIKUCHIYO] Thanks to me your
search is officially done.

150
00:09:18,083 --> 00:09:19,291
Look, Kambei...!

151
00:09:19,375 --> 00:09:22,041
Now you can have
your pick of the litter... 

152
00:09:22,125 --> 00:09:24,750
Almost too much
to take in, isn't it?

153
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:26,291
That's one way to put it!

154
00:09:26,375 --> 00:09:27,291
[KIKUCHIYO] What?!

155
00:09:27,375 --> 00:09:29,041
And just where
did you find them?

156
00:09:29,125 --> 00:09:31,083
[KIKUCHIYO]
I broke them out of jail.

157
00:09:31,166 --> 00:09:32,625
[GOROBEI SIGHS]

158
00:09:32,708 --> 00:09:35,125
[GOROBEI]
Losers, every last one of 'em.

159
00:09:35,208 --> 00:09:37,875
What did you say?!

160
00:09:39,125 --> 00:09:40,041
Draw...!

161
00:09:40,125 --> 00:09:41,250
You won't think
we're such losers

162
00:09:41,333 --> 00:09:43,166
once you're lying
face down in the dirt!

163
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:45,500
[KIKUCHIYO]
Whoa whoa whoa, relax!

164
00:09:52,166 --> 00:09:57,125
[SAMURAI GROUP YELLS]

165
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:07,708
[SAMURAI GROUP GROANS]

166
00:10:10,750 --> 00:10:12,541
[KAMBEI]
You see? Useless.

167
00:10:12,625 --> 00:10:14,208
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

168
00:10:14,291 --> 00:10:19,125
[MASAMUNE] You sure know how
to attract attention, Kiku.

169
00:10:19,208 --> 00:10:21,791
Let's go...
they'll be coming soon.

170
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:28,875
[KAMBEI] We must act
wisely, and with speed.

171
00:10:28,958 --> 00:10:30,250
[GOROBEI]
The Magistrate's patrolmen

172
00:10:30,333 --> 00:10:32,083
will be coming from
the upper tiers.

173
00:10:32,166 --> 00:10:34,791
We should work our way down
to the lower parts of the city.

174
00:10:34,875 --> 00:10:35,875
Stay ahead of them.

175
00:10:35,958 --> 00:10:37,708
That seems
too obvious.

176
00:10:37,791 --> 00:10:38,875
[GOROBEI]
You have concerns?

177
00:10:38,958 --> 00:10:40,125
They'll be
expecting it.

178
00:10:40,208 --> 00:10:42,041
All of the checkpoints
will be guarded.

179
00:10:42,125 --> 00:10:43,083
[KAMBEI]
Would you happen to know

180
00:10:43,166 --> 00:10:44,750
of a less conspicuous route?

181
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:47,166
Hmm...

182
00:10:47,250 --> 00:10:49,666
We might be able to use
the old elevator train.

183
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:51,541
I'm not familiar with it.

184
00:10:51,625 --> 00:10:53,375
[MASAMUNE] It's a freight lift
they used to run between

185
00:10:53,458 --> 00:10:55,250
the old ground city
and the top...

186
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:57,500
but I'm not even sure
if it's still working.

187
00:10:57,583 --> 00:10:59,541
[KIKUCHIYO] Great!
What are we waiting for?!

188
00:10:59,625 --> 00:11:01,708
[GOROBEI] Since when
do you make the decisions?

189
00:11:01,791 --> 00:11:03,458
[KIKUCHIYO]
Somebody's got to!

190
00:11:03,541 --> 00:11:05,125
[KAMBEI]
Let's go.

191
00:11:05,208 --> 00:11:07,750
At present we have
no other option.

192
00:11:15,125 --> 00:11:17,458
I want you to make sure you
keep up with everyone, Komachi.

193
00:11:17,541 --> 00:11:19,625
We can't have you
holding us up, okay?

194
00:11:19,708 --> 00:11:22,458
Relax--I'm the
fastest kid I know!

195
00:11:22,541 --> 00:11:24,791
We're leaving here with
only three true samurai--

196
00:11:24,875 --> 00:11:26,416
At this rate I don't know
how we're going to find

197
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:28,166
enough to protect the village.

198
00:11:28,250 --> 00:11:30,708
[KOMACHI]
You mustn't lose hope.

199
00:11:30,791 --> 00:11:32,166
[KOMACHI GIGGLES]

200
00:11:32,250 --> 00:11:34,125
I sounded like sister, huh?

201
00:11:41,625 --> 00:11:43,041
I know it's a lot
to ask, Sensei,

202
00:11:43,125 --> 00:11:46,000
but do you think it would
be alright if I came with you?

203
00:11:46,083 --> 00:11:49,000
I suppose
you'll have to.

204
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,708
Do not
misunderstand...

205
00:11:50,791 --> 00:11:52,333
as long as you and
Kikuchiyo insist on

206
00:11:52,416 --> 00:11:54,125
passing yourselves
off as samurai,

207
00:11:54,208 --> 00:11:57,666
remaining here will
only endanger Masamune.

208
00:11:57,750 --> 00:11:58,958
[KIKUCHIYO]
Don't sweat it, Katsu,

209
00:11:59,041 --> 00:12:01,041
I know he doesn't think
we're real samurai.

210
00:12:01,125 --> 00:12:03,875
But he'll change his
mind soon enough.

211
00:12:03,958 --> 00:12:06,333
I'll bring up the rear!

212
00:12:07,541 --> 00:12:09,833
Oh, yeah, now that's
what I call a samurai.

213
00:12:09,916 --> 00:12:12,250
[KIKUCHIYO] Heh, heh...
At least you get me!

214
00:12:12,333 --> 00:12:13,625
[GOROBEI]
They're here.

215
00:12:15,125 --> 00:12:16,708
[MASAMUNE]
This way!

216
00:12:18,541 --> 00:12:20,291
[KIKUCHIYO GRUNTS]

217
00:12:20,375 --> 00:12:21,500
[KIRARA]
You ready?

218
00:12:21,583 --> 00:12:22,583
[KOMACHI] Yep.

219
00:12:28,875 --> 00:12:29,833
[PATROLMAN A]
The informants reported

220
00:12:29,916 --> 00:12:31,083
several veteran samurai

221
00:12:31,166 --> 00:12:33,416
were hiding out in here,
so keep your guard up.

222
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:34,750
Let's go.

223
00:12:36,958 --> 00:12:40,625
[CRASHING SOUND]

224
00:12:42,041 --> 00:12:44,708
[PATROLMAN A] Samurai!
We know you're in here!

225
00:13:40,958 --> 00:13:42,208
Hmm...?

226
00:13:42,291 --> 00:13:43,125
[THUD]

227
00:13:43,208 --> 00:13:44,250
Ow!

228
00:14:10,333 --> 00:14:12,166
[HEIHACHI] Here.

229
00:14:12,250 --> 00:14:13,458
[KOMACHI] Thanks.

230
00:14:13,541 --> 00:14:14,875
I gotcha!

231
00:14:16,708 --> 00:14:17,666
Uh...!

232
00:14:18,875 --> 00:14:20,500
[KIKUCHIYO]
Oh, you alright?

233
00:14:20,583 --> 00:14:21,791
Yeah... I'm good.

234
00:14:21,875 --> 00:14:24,166
[KOMACHI] It's not easy
being the new guy.

235
00:14:30,583 --> 00:14:32,125
[PATROLMAN C] We've pulled
up the maps of this area.

236
00:14:32,208 --> 00:14:34,125
There's an old
elevator train nearby.

237
00:14:34,208 --> 00:14:36,166
[PATROLMAN A]
Let's check it out.

238
00:14:41,458 --> 00:14:45,625
[KIKUCHIYO] Uh... You sure
this piece of junk is safe?

239
00:14:45,708 --> 00:14:48,375
[MASAMUNE]
Uh...

240
00:14:48,458 --> 00:14:50,208
Heihachi,
come with me.

241
00:14:50,291 --> 00:14:51,916
Sure. Right behind you.

242
00:14:53,708 --> 00:14:55,416
Is everybody ready for this?

243
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:56,833
[KIRARA] Yes.

244
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,291
[GOROBEI]
Come on, we'll be on lookout.

245
00:14:59,375 --> 00:15:00,750
[KIKUCHIYO] Right!

246
00:15:03,041 --> 00:15:04,958
[KIKUCHIYO]
Well, they're here!

247
00:15:05,041 --> 00:15:06,500
[KAMBEI]
Masamune!

248
00:15:06,583 --> 00:15:08,958
[MASAMUNE] These things
take some time you know!

249
00:15:09,041 --> 00:15:10,750
How's it coming kid?

250
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:12,916
Do you think we'll be
able to get her started?

251
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,708
I'm not too
worried about it.

252
00:15:14,791 --> 00:15:16,208
Huh...?

253
00:15:16,291 --> 00:15:17,916
We'll get down one
way or another.

254
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,750
Whatever will be,
will be.

255
00:15:19,833 --> 00:15:21,875
[KIKUCHIYO GRUNTS]

256
00:15:21,958 --> 00:15:24,583
[GOROBEI] Hey! You wanna bet
you don't make it in time?

257
00:15:24,666 --> 00:15:26,583
[KIKUCHIYO]
Shut your face!

258
00:15:30,625 --> 00:15:32,000
[KIKUCHIYO SIGHS]

259
00:15:32,083 --> 00:15:33,291
[GOROBEI]
Let's go!

260
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,750
Welcome
aboard, folks!

261
00:15:36,833 --> 00:15:38,500
Well, this is where
we part ways.

262
00:15:38,583 --> 00:15:41,166
[KAMBEI] Someday I'll
repay this debt. I promise.

263
00:15:41,250 --> 00:15:43,125
[MASAMUNE] Wh-What the hell
are you doing that for?!

264
00:15:43,208 --> 00:15:44,458
It's for your own good.

265
00:15:44,541 --> 00:15:45,666
There will be less trouble
for you if they think

266
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:47,375
we forced you
into helping us.

267
00:15:47,458 --> 00:15:49,666
Oh I see, thanks Kambei.

268
00:15:49,750 --> 00:15:50,875
[MASAMUNE YELLS]

269
00:15:50,958 --> 00:15:53,500
It's pointless if
it doesn't look real.

270
00:15:53,583 --> 00:15:57,333
[KIKUCHIYO] Yeah, I better rough
him up a little, too. Heh...

271
00:15:57,416 --> 00:15:59,666
No way...!
You get away from me!

272
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:01,291
[KIKUCHIYO]
C'mon! I'll be gentle.

273
00:16:01,375 --> 00:16:03,208
Ahh! Kiku!

274
00:16:03,291 --> 00:16:04,791
[BLOWS LANDING]

275
00:16:09,625 --> 00:16:11,708
[MASAMUNE YELLS]

276
00:16:11,791 --> 00:16:14,833
You... I'm not going
to forget this! Ahh!

277
00:16:16,208 --> 00:16:18,500
[KIKUCHIYO] Looks like I
need to buy some time.

278
00:16:18,583 --> 00:16:20,000
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

279
00:16:20,083 --> 00:16:22,166
Just try to get past me!

280
00:16:22,250 --> 00:16:23,333
[KAMBEI]
Kikuchiyo!

281
00:16:23,416 --> 00:16:25,375
[KIKUCHIYO]
Go! I'll catch up.

282
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:27,541
[HEIHACHI GRUNTS]

283
00:16:32,833 --> 00:16:33,875
[MASAMUNE YELLS]

284
00:16:34,666 --> 00:16:36,208
[KIKUCHIYO]
Anybody else?!

285
00:16:36,291 --> 00:16:38,000
Well, in that case...

286
00:16:38,083 --> 00:16:38,875
[PATROLMEN] Huh...?!

287
00:16:38,958 --> 00:16:41,250
[KIKUCHIYO]
See ya, suckers!

288
00:16:41,333 --> 00:16:42,416
What do we do now?

289
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:44,166
Light up the beacon!

290
00:16:51,333 --> 00:16:52,291
[PATROLMEN] Go!

291
00:16:59,375 --> 00:17:00,291
[GOROBEI]
Are you all right?

292
00:17:00,375 --> 00:17:01,875
[KIKUCHIYO]
Damn right I am.

293
00:17:01,958 --> 00:17:03,291
[SCREECHING]

294
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:06,750
[KOMACHI GASPS]

295
00:17:23,541 --> 00:17:25,125
[MASAMUNE THINKING]
Kambei, my friend...

296
00:17:25,208 --> 00:17:27,916
may fortune be with you.

297
00:17:40,125 --> 00:17:41,500
[KAMBEI]
Katsushiro, take the villagers

298
00:17:41,583 --> 00:17:42,916
to the passenger car.

299
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,208
Right.

300
00:17:47,250 --> 00:17:50,750
I think your friend here's
going to be quite useful.

301
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:52,916
We need to cut
the passenger car.

302
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:55,000
Go outside and
attach this to it.

303
00:17:55,083 --> 00:17:57,208
[HEIHACHI]
I am all over it.

304
00:18:01,750 --> 00:18:04,583
[KIKUCHIYO] I was wondering
what was taking them so long!

305
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:06,833
You have got
to be kidding me.

306
00:18:10,125 --> 00:18:11,750
Kikuchiyo!

307
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:14,541
[KIKUCHIYO] Relax, you can leave
those hunters to me, Boss-man!

308
00:18:14,625 --> 00:18:17,500
[KAMBEI] Good to know,
but I need one more thing.

309
00:18:17,583 --> 00:18:20,708
On my signal, reel this
in as hard as you can.

310
00:18:20,791 --> 00:18:22,125
[KIKUCHIYO]
Okay...

311
00:18:22,208 --> 00:18:24,000
Don't have a clue what
you're doing, but you got it!

312
00:18:29,791 --> 00:18:31,375
[KIKUCHIYO]
Here we go!

313
00:18:31,458 --> 00:18:32,666
[KAMBEI]
You set?

314
00:18:32,750 --> 00:18:33,875
[KIKUCHIYO] Yeah!

315
00:18:39,958 --> 00:18:41,291
That'll do.

316
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:47,083
We ready?

317
00:18:47,166 --> 00:18:48,583
Ready as we'll ever be.

318
00:18:48,666 --> 00:18:50,041
Good. Disconnect it.

319
00:18:50,125 --> 00:18:51,083
Right.

320
00:18:54,333 --> 00:18:56,750
[KAMBEI] On my cue,
start the smoke-screen.

321
00:18:56,833 --> 00:18:59,041
Sure thing!
I'm on it!

322
00:19:10,958 --> 00:19:14,500
[BEEPING]

323
00:19:14,583 --> 00:19:16,541
[SCREECHING]

324
00:19:18,125 --> 00:19:19,583
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

325
00:19:21,875 --> 00:19:22,833
[PATROLMAN A SCREAMS]

326
00:19:46,833 --> 00:19:48,291
Let's do it.

327
00:19:50,125 --> 00:19:51,791
[EXPLOSION]

328
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:54,875
Kikuchiyo... Gorobei!

329
00:19:57,166 --> 00:19:58,083
PATROLMAN B SCREAMS]

330
00:19:58,166 --> 00:19:59,833
[GOROBEI]
Kikuchiyo! The cable!

331
00:19:59,916 --> 00:20:01,000
[KIKUCHIYO] On it!

332
00:20:04,375 --> 00:20:07,708
[KIKUCHIYO] You go ahead...
I got a handle on all this!

333
00:20:07,791 --> 00:20:10,000
Once you finish reeling...
get down here quick...

334
00:20:10,083 --> 00:20:11,416
...you got it?

335
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:12,625
[KIKUCHIYO] Gotcha!

336
00:20:12,708 --> 00:20:14,125
[KIKUCHIYO GRUNTS]

337
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:19,333
Come on, I dare you.

338
00:20:24,583 --> 00:20:27,708
[HEIHACHI] Hey Kambei, 
I finally see what you're up to.

339
00:20:29,791 --> 00:20:30,416
[KAMBEI]
Katsushiro.

340
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:31,500
Yes?

341
00:20:31,583 --> 00:20:32,958
As soon as the
train reduces its speed,

342
00:20:33,041 --> 00:20:34,958
we're going to jump
onto the platform.

343
00:20:35,041 --> 00:20:36,166
Understood.

344
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:37,333
[KOMACHI YELLS]

345
00:20:38,625 --> 00:20:39,875
[KIKUCHIYO]
Ah! Piece of junk!

346
00:20:39,958 --> 00:20:42,875
Looks like I'm gonna have
to do this the hard way!

347
00:20:45,125 --> 00:20:46,958
I don't have time for this!

348
00:20:47,041 --> 00:20:48,333
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

349
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:55,833
Prepare yourselves!

350
00:21:02,750 --> 00:21:03,875
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

351
00:21:08,750 --> 00:21:09,791
You ready for this?

352
00:21:09,875 --> 00:21:11,000
Yeah!

353
00:21:12,416 --> 00:21:14,250
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS FRANTICALLY]

354
00:21:14,333 --> 00:21:16,291
[KAMBEI] Now!

355
00:21:16,375 --> 00:21:17,750
[KATSUSHIRO] Hurry!

356
00:21:23,208 --> 00:21:25,958
[KAMBEI] Kikuchiyo, that's
good-- jump to the platform!

357
00:21:26,041 --> 00:21:28,208
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS FRANTICALLY]

358
00:21:29,208 --> 00:21:30,333
[KIKUCHIYO] Hold on!

359
00:21:30,416 --> 00:21:31,833
[KATSUSHIRO] Sensei!

360
00:21:40,833 --> 00:21:42,875
[GOROBEI]
Forget them! Come on!

361
00:21:42,958 --> 00:21:44,416
Kikuchiyo!

362
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:46,291
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

363
00:21:46,375 --> 00:21:48,333
[KIKUCHIYO]
You better not screw this up!

364
00:21:48,416 --> 00:21:50,958
Save those farmers, okay!

365
00:21:54,083 --> 00:21:56,625
[SCREECHING]

366
00:22:00,833 --> 00:22:03,291
[KIKUCHIYO SCREAMS]

367
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:31,208
[KAMBEI] Let's go.

368
00:22:31,291 --> 00:22:33,416
But Kikuchiyo-dono...

369
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:36,125
Sensei...
This isn't like you!

370
00:22:36,208 --> 00:22:38,125
[KAMBEI]
In my life...

371
00:22:38,208 --> 00:22:42,166
I've had to step over
many an ally's corpse...

372
00:22:42,250 --> 00:22:44,833
That is the kind of man I am.

373
00:22:48,166 --> 00:22:49,583
Komachi!

374
00:22:54,041 --> 00:22:56,208
I won't let you!

375
00:22:56,291 --> 00:23:02,250
[KOMACHI SOBS]

376
00:23:02,333 --> 00:23:04,541
I won't let you leave him!

377
00:23:04,625 --> 00:23:07,458
I won't let you leave Kiku!

378
00:23:07,541 --> 00:23:11,083
[KOMACHI CRIES]

379
00:23:13,166 --> 00:23:18,125
♪ closing song ♪

380
00:25:22,416 --> 00:25:24,208
[KOMACHI]
Hey Okara, it's me again.

381
00:25:24,291 --> 00:25:26,416
Things have been
going terribly here!

382
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:29,083
One minute everything
seems okay, then the next

383
00:25:29,166 --> 00:25:31,500
we're wanted criminals running
from these really mean,

384
00:25:31,583 --> 00:25:34,333
weird looking guys
with big, sharp sticks!

385
00:25:34,416 --> 00:25:37,333
It has something to do with
this whole samurai hunt,

386
00:25:37,416 --> 00:25:38,416
though I don't know why,

387
00:25:38,500 --> 00:25:40,666
since we haven't done
anything wrong.

388
00:25:40,750 --> 00:25:43,375
So now it looks like we'll be
returning to the village soon,

389
00:25:43,458 --> 00:25:45,958
even though we don't
have all seven samurai.

390
00:25:46,041 --> 00:25:47,875
But that's not the worst of it!

391
00:25:47,958 --> 00:25:49,875
We were on this
big scary train,

392
00:25:49,958 --> 00:25:52,375
trying to get away from
those mean men, you know,

393
00:25:52,458 --> 00:25:54,291
and Kiku was being really brave

394
00:25:54,375 --> 00:25:56,625
and fighting them off
so we would be safe,

395
00:25:56,708 --> 00:25:58,416
but he didn't jump from
the train in time

396
00:25:58,500 --> 00:26:01,416
and now I don't think I'll
ever get to see him again!

397
00:26:01,500 --> 00:26:04,291
And stupid Kambei never
gave Kiku any credit,

398
00:26:04,375 --> 00:26:07,541
even though he was the most
bravest samurai that ever lived!

399
00:26:07,625 --> 00:26:11,375
Kambei didn't even care when
Kiku disappeared in the crash!

400
00:26:11,458 --> 00:26:14,875
Okay, well I guess I'm going
to cry myself to sleep now...

401
00:26:14,958 --> 00:26:16,250
Bye bye.

